nodes.text: Zoochberry dumplings were a type of food that was made from Zoochberries, a type of fruit, and was edible for members of the Hutt species. They were served by the Prophets of the Dark Side, a dark side cult, at a banquet held to celebrate a visit from the Hutt crime lord Zorba Desilijic Tiure in 5 ABY. While eating the dumplings at the banquet, Zorba spilled some on the robes of the High Prophet Jedgar, which left stains on his clothes.
Zoochberry dumplings appeared in Prophets of the Dark Side, the sixth and final novel in the Jedi Prince series, written by Paul Davids and Hollace Davids, and released in 1993.
